Stoudemire, Douglas Score 24 Points Each as Knicks Defeat Hornets 107-88

-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 
2011-03-03T05:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/stoudemire-douglas-score-24-points-each-as-knicks-defeat-hornets-107-88.html
Amar’e Stoudemire and Toney Douglas
each scored 24 points and  Carmelo Anthony  added 22 in the  New
York  Knicks’ 107-88 win against the New Orleans Hornets in a
National Basketball Association contest.  Shawne Williams had 16 points and Landry Fields tallied 10
for the Knicks (31-28), who handed the Hornets (35-28) their
third straight loss.  Jarrett Jack had 21 points and David West had 16 for the
Hornets at Madison Square Garden in New York.  The Knicks are in sixth place in the Eastern Conference and
are second to the Boston Celtics (44-15) in the Atlantic
Division.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
